…..the adventure of  a much too @#%$y youngster….<br>
<br>
Ravapalic<br>
Level 12 Rogue of Povar<br>
<br>
I slip into the castle. (Never leave your party dummy).  Ease around the corner to the throne room.  A couple of folks are camping. Camping for Emperor Crush?  I yell: “Where are you guys?” <br>
<br>
“We’re inside, against the back wall.”  Isn’t that what I heard?  (NEVER leave your party.) Yes, I’m sure that’s what I heard.  I boldly walk past the table, by the throne behind the throne to the back wall.  Where are the guys?  (NEVER I said NEVER leave your party.)<br>
<br>
WHAM.  Behind me.  An Oracle.  Quick - retreat to the entrance.  WHAM. A Royal Guard with the Oracle.  Crap.  Holly Crap, I’m in it deep.  WHERE ARE YOU GUYS. And the campers watch casually .. hell I was there to steal there kill anyway (so they muse) and maybe my agony will speed the Crush along. WHAM .. BANG .. WHACK.. I’m down to 1/3 of my health already and the two lugs are IN FRONT now - between me and the hall.  Cant go around. Wait. What’s happening? I’m spinning around..stunned. WHACK WHACK.  There’s the window. Go for it. <br>
<br>
I dive through the window headfirst.  Tumble on the grass and rocks and trip..  SPLASH. DAMN.  What happened?  I’m in water.  Must have tripped into the canal. Swim. Get your head up.  Swim.  God, I’m encumbered. I can’t surface.  What was that; what was that I heard?  A splash behind me?  No it can’t be. Oh no. WHAM WHACK.  I’m down to a bub. I’m drowning.  Ok I’m a goner I’ll go down fighting.  Stand up Rav. Hit auto attack.  Turn around.  Look at the bast*** in the eye. OK navel.  Oh this is sweet , the last thing I’m gonna  see is an Orc’s belly! The turkey is standing under water.  Standing on the bottom of the canal whaling away. I wonder if he’s drowning. Yeah, right. The putrid spawn of bat dung. I feebly pierce. I’m choking.  I AM DROWNING.   where are you guys? WHACK…oh sweet Jesus.. hit /loc…did it register?  WHACK…where are…gurggle..glug.. where are… blackness<br>
<br>
NEVER NEVER NEVER  LEAVE YOUR PARTY ***HOLE.  I’m dead and I deserve it and I am ashamed and humiliated.  BUT YOUR PARTY DOESN’T DESERVE IT BUTTHEAD. DAMN DAMN DAMN.<br>
<br>
OK. Get back in there and find your body and re-up. Pronto. Get going.  Laliani is shouting at you “Are you ok Rav?  Where are you?”   I should answer.  But I’m ticked at myself.  And didn’t she see the life blood flow out of my meter like damned Niagara Falls?  I’m alright, about as alright as a naked stupid lvl 12 has a right to be.  OK push  out fast, talk later.  Your team is fighting. Push on.<br>
<br>
Through CB; put it in sneak and hide and make your way to the loc.  Past Orc and fighter.  Stay focused (“Where are you Rav.”)  Right hear.  No I don’t say that I think it.  Don’t bug me.  I’m busy I don’t need help.  No I don’t say that.  I think it.  (“Need help Rav where are you?”)  No. I don’t need help.  Piece of cake.  I’ll get the body and join up and explain.  Right here wasn’t it?  Yes.  This is right /loc.  Lean over.  And hit /corpse and. SPLASH.  What?  I FELL IN DAMNIT TO HELL I FELL IN. Swim you idiot.  “Rav, are you ok”.  CRAP No.  NO!  I’m not ok.  But I can’t  talk and swim at the same time.  Can I swim? No? Yes. YES!! Relief.  Its working now. Swimming.  Find a ladder. Where are they? “Tell us where you are and we will come Rav.” How the hell can I tell you when I don’t know I DON’T KNOW.  Cant talk and swim (glug..swallowed water) at same time anyway.  A ladder.  Great now climb out.  Ugh.  Slimey. Its slippery.  I’ve fallen back in.. again..and again.. swim around and make another approach.. where am I.  Oh there it is - grab it head on ..aalllmosttt up.   SPLASH fell backwaaardd…oh oh oh im getting tired and weak.. circle again..grab it.  Drag yourself out.  At last I’m out.  I’m wet and cold and hungry and miserable.  Where am I? Where are those guys when I need them (** ok I KNOW that is a most unfair and irrational thought** but I’m tired and wet, and miserable and feeling sorry for myself.  And mad at my stupidness**). Stand up and look around.  I’m dizzy.  Its dark.  SPLASH.  Oh no no NO NO.. Learn Rav.  Learn.  Swim out and turn around and approach it head on there’s a trick to this..grab it; ugh..slippery.  Do it again.. Haul yourself out you miserable excuse for a Rogue.  On land again.  Wet.  cold.  hungry.  Demoralized. Whats this?  Thirsty too?? Now that’s ironic.  Where am I?  Ok I think I am by the orc camp.  Sneak, mode.  Creep back. Slink back.  It’s a wonder the stupid Orcs don’t follow the trail of water.  My feet are cold, squish squish.<br>
<br>
Finally.  Back at /loc.  BE CAREFUL. Don’t fall in again clutz. /corpse.  No corpse. I’m sure it’s the right place. Walk up and down hitting /corpse. Nothing. What gives?  Could I have written the loc down wrong?  Scroll up and check it.  Cant scroll - whats wrong?  LINK DEAD.  OH NO NOT NOW.  I’m QUITTING. I HATE THIS GAME. I’m gonna use the EQ CD as a freekin FRISBEE!!  Im stomping on it!!! I HATE THIS.  I’m.. I’m…sigh… ok .. I’m gonna reboot.<br>
<br>
Back.  Sit down rav and think.  Gather your wits.  Quit panicking. I am pretty sure..yes VERY sure I have the right /loc. Hell cant check; had to reboot.  Gotta assume its  right. So the /corpse didn’t work.  Maybe you gotta be on top of your corpse for it to work. Or like see it. Did you see your body?  No.  But I could only really see the other side.  I could creep up an lean over.. NO. I’ve swum enough tonight. Don’t want to lean over to far and fall in again. I’ve got it!  I’ll cross the bridge, try from the other side. Creeping. Creeping.. OK this is about the right place. Whats that?  Looks like a black gauntleted hand sticking out of the wall. No body.  Just a hand.  Could it be? Click it.  JOY!! it says RAVAPALIC.  OK calm down. Look around.  Don’t blow it now. Looks safe.  Its quiet. Dawn.  The filthy Orcs are less active now.  That’s lucky.   Lets try  /loot.  JOY IT WORKS! Rob.  Dry off. Time to re-join.  These ugly crusts of wolf dung will pay!  THEY WILL PAY!<br>
<br>
Hey, it aint such a bad game after all! <br>
<br>
But… did you learn anything.  Yep lots.  But mainly Don’t EVER,  EVER leave your group again bonehead!!<br>
<br>
